				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.silverstream.com/products/main/main_f.htm&quot;&gt;SilverStream&lt;/a&gt; looks very interesting."/>
				</outline>
			<outline text="November 19" created="Wed, 19 Nov 1997 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="James Gosling is PC Mag's &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zdnet.com/pcmag/special/techex97/tx97_poy.htm&quot;&gt;person of the year&lt;/a&gt;.">
					<outline text="And guess who got the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zdnet.com/pcmag/special/techex97/tx97_life.htm&quot;&gt;lifetime achievement award&lt;/a&gt;."/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="While things are slower now, why not read &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/randomPages.get.fcgi$DaveNet;10;&quot;&gt;10 Random DaveNets&lt;/a&gt;?"/>
				<outline text="Apple &lt;a href=&quot;http://biz.yahoo.com/finance/971118/computers_apple_1.html&quot;&gt;donates&lt;/a&gt; its history to Stanford. &lt;i&gt;Good move!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
				<outline text="The Atlantic Monthly &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.theatlantic.com/unbound/digicult/dc9711.htm&quot;&gt;reviews&lt;/a&gt; Riven."/>
				<outline text="Reading &lt;A HREF=&quot;http://ws3.scripting.com/register/&quot;&gt;the regcards&lt;/A&gt;, ">
					<outline text="we learned that a bunch of people are intimidated by the techy discussions on the main Frontier mailing lists."/>
					<outline text="So we started the &lt;A HREF=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/lists/FrontierNewbies.html&quot;&gt;Frontier-newbies&lt;/A&gt; "/>
					<outline text="list, moderated by Thea Partridge, with a unique approach, a commitment to keep it focused on the easy and simple stuff."/>
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Still diggin!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="If you're using Frontier on one of the new G3 Macs you definitely need ">
					<outline text="&lt;A HREF=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/frontier/newReleases/9600fix.html&quot;&gt;the 9600 fix&lt;/A&gt; "/>
					<outline text="released on 9/12/97."/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="November 18" created="Tue, 18 Nov 1997 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="I received three pieces of email today from people who are concerned that">
					<outline text="there won't be a free version of Frontier 5. Don't worry. At some point in the "/>
					<outline text="future there may be a commercial release of Frontier, but there will absolutely "/>
					<outline text="be a free release of Frontier 5. There may be a feature set that's commercial,"/>
					<outline text="but that hasn't been decided yet."/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="A &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/images/canters.jpg&quot;&gt;picture&lt;/a&gt; taken at Sunday's 49ers game in SF. ">
					<outline text="That's me in the foreground (looking serious!) and Aryeh, Jacob and Marc Canter in the background."/>
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Go Niners!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.techconsulting.com/sean/&quot;&gt;A great Frontier site&lt;/a&gt;. &lt;i&gt;You'll laugh!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
				<outline text="PC WEEK: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zdnet.com/pcweek/news/1117/18edoj.html&quot;&gt;Gates says DOJ action could kill Windows&lt;/a&gt;. ">
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Don't worry Bill, we'll save it!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="CNN: &lt;a href=&quot;http://cnn.com/TECH/9711/18/comdex.ibm.car.reut/index.html&quot;&gt;IBM shows Internet-ready car&lt;/a&gt;. ">
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Is it scriptable?&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Slate &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.slate.com/BookReview/97-11-18/BookReview.asp&quot;&gt;reviews&lt;/a&gt; Esther Dyson's new book."/>
				<outline text="Was it worth the effort to port Frontier to Windows? Read on..."/>
				<outline text="From a Sun engineer who's been playing with Frontier 5.0a16/Win:">
					<outline text="&quot;I am ... blown away is the right way to describe my feeling. In fact, it's"/>
					<outline text="eerily like when I first discovered Emacs. At that time I wrote a congrat"/>
					<outline text="email to James Gosling, and now I'm writing one to you! This is a winner"/>
					<outline text="idea. Having an ODB with a name space and stored scripts and the scripts"/>
					<outline text="have access to the name space directly. First time I heard about it I said,"/>
					<outline text="yeah sure that's nice, it just didn't hit home how powerful this is until I"/>
					<outline text="actually used it.&quot; &lt;i&gt;That feels so incredibly good!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="The answer is yes, it was worth the trouble. &lt;i&gt;Let's have fun!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
				<outline text="Here's a list of all the &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/lists/&quot;&gt;UserLand-hosted mail lists&lt;/a&gt;, on one page."/>
				<outline text="Two new lists: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/lists/Announcements.html&quot;&gt;Scripting Announcements&lt;/a&gt; and ">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/lists/FrontierNewbies.html&quot;&gt;Frontier-newbies&lt;/a&gt;."/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Our mail server, mail.scripting.com, was off the air, but it's back now."/>
				</outline>
			<outline text="November 17" created="Mon, 17 Nov 1997 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="DaveNet: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/davenet/97/11/onceAWeek.html&quot;&gt;Once A Week&lt;/a&gt;."/>
				<outline text="A redesign of my &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/dwiner/&quot;&gt;personal website&lt;/a&gt;, including ">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/dwiner/historyOfFrontier.html&quot;&gt;part two&lt;/a&gt; of my life as a software developer, "/>
					<outline text="a site &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/dwiner/outline.html&quot;&gt;outline&lt;/a&gt; and "/>
					<outline text="a &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/dwiner/siteShot.html&quot;&gt;screen shot&lt;/a&gt; of my Windows NT work environment."/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Here's what &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/dwiner/images/solitaire&quot;&gt;Solitaire&lt;/a&gt; looks like just as you're about to win."/>
				<outline text="Wired's Jeff Veen on the ">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/davenet/stories/veenOnWebmonkeyRedesign.html&quot;&gt;WebMonkey redesign&lt;/a&gt;."/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Jakob Nielsen &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.useit.com/alertbox/9711b.html&quot;&gt;reviews&lt;/a&gt; Esther Dyson's new book."/>
				<outline text="ABC News: &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.abcnews.com/sections/scitech/moody28/index.html&quot;&gt;Gates’ Internet Fiction&lt;/a&gt;."/>
				<outline text="In October 1994, Gates &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/davenet/94/10/replyfrombillgates.html&quot;&gt;responded&lt;/a&gt;">
					<outline text="to an early DaveNet piece about Microsoft and the Internet."/>
					<outline text="Re-reading his response in late 1997, yes, I think he was reasonably clued in about the net in 1994. "/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="In July 1997, Jacob Levy, an engineer at Sun ">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/davenet/stories/JacobLevyRespondstoDoc.html&quot;&gt;wrote an interesting email&lt;/a&gt; "/>
					<outline text="about Bill Gates. &lt;i&gt;Summary: he's Salieri, not Mozart.&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.news.com/News/Item/0,4,16427,00.html&quot;&gt;News.com&lt;/a&gt;: ">
					<outline text="A great RealAudio &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.news.com/Rams/November_97/11_16_97/doj.ram&quot;&gt;soundbite&lt;/a&gt; "/>
					<outline text="from Gates's Comdex keynote yesterday."/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="A new HyperCard &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.glasscat.com/list/HCML.cgi&quot;&gt;mailing list&lt;/a&gt;."/>
				<outline text="Oooops! ">
					<outline text="For about 30 minutes this morning the home page here contained the home page text for my personal site."/>
					<outline text="That's the trouble with powerful tools, you can make powerful mistakes!"/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="November 16" created="Sun, 16 Nov 1997 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="http://www.macwindows.com/"/>
				<outline text="Guy Kawasaki took a trip to Fallon McElligot in the summer of 1996. ">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.evangelist.macaddict.com/gallery/fallon.html&quot;&gt;He took pictures&lt;/a&gt;, "/>
					<outline text="including one of Matthew Dornquast, the web developer "/>
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/davenet/stories/DornquastProfile.html&quot;&gt;we profiled&lt;/a&gt; "/>
					<outline text="last week. If you look closely you can see WebSTAR and Frontier on the screen of their Macs."/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Here's a chance to do some collaborative development. ">
					<outline text="We need &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/gimme5/Stories/dlls.html&quot;&gt;a DLL&lt;/a&gt; to "/>
					<outline text="connect Frontier 5/Win to web browsers. "/>
					<outline text="Spyglass &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.spyglass.com/products/smosaic/sdi/sdi%5Fspec.html&quot;&gt;posted docs&lt;/a&gt; for a standard interface "/>
					<outline text="thru TCP, Apple Events, and DDE. "/>
					<outline text="We believe this interface is supported by both Netscape and Microsoft."/>
					<outline text="We already have the Apple Event interface for Frontier/Mac."/>
					<outline text="We want to get a similar suite working with the Windows product. "/>
					<outline text="We think the source code for the DDE interface on Windows should be public. "/>
					<outline text="Anyone want to do this? &lt;i&gt;We'll get to it eventually if no one does it.&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="IBM has an interesting website that includes information on how the ">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.redbooks.ibm.com/SG244230/sg244209.htm&quot;&gt;Smalltalk environment&lt;/a&gt; works."/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="November 15" created="Sat, 15 Nov 1997 05:00:01 GMT">
				<outline text="If you use Frontier, please visit  ">
					<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.scripting.com/davenet/stories/userlandneedsyourhelp.html&quot;&gt;this page&lt;/a&gt;."/>
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;Thanks!&lt;/i&gt;"/>
					</outline>
				<outline text="&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hotwired.com/webmonkey/&quot;&gt;WebMonkey&lt;/a&gt; did a site redesign. ">
					<outline text="&lt;i&gt;What do you think?&lt;/i&gt;&lt;ol&gt;"/>
					<outline text="&lt;p&gt;">
						<outline text="&lt;li&gt;The new site structure -- a home page showing all the current stories, and an archive listing"/>
						<outline text="all the older stories, grouped by categories. Every page links to all the categories."/>
						<outline text="&lt;p&gt;"/>
						<outline text="&lt;li&gt;Ideally, sites like this would have an index, like the index in the back of a reference book. I've often thought "/>
						<outline text="it would be interesting to have an index like this for &quot;DaveNet&quot;."/>
						<outline text="&lt;p&gt;"/>
						<outline text="&lt;li&gt;I find it confusing that the home page uses a different template from the other pages. Also, instead of "/>
						<outline text="repeating the navigation bar at the top of the 2nd level pages, they run it down the left edge. There's an"/>
						<outline text="interesting effect tied to the home page navigation section, and a gorgeous graphic of an on/off switch."/>
						<outline text="&lt;p&gt;"/>
						<outline text="&lt;li&gt;If you switch the switch off, you get a picture of Jeffrey Veen, lookin a little geeky, &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hotwired.com/webmonkey/97/45/index0a.html&quot;&gt;explaining&lt;/a&gt;"/>
						<outline text="why they did the redesign (an interesting piece, definitely worth a read). But... why did turning the switch off"/>
						<outline text="get me to this page? And what is its relationship to the other pages on the site?"/>
						<outline text="&lt;p&gt;"/>
						<outline text="&lt;li&gt;The &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.hotwired.com/webmonkey/97/45/index0a_page4.html&quot;&gt;metadata system&lt;/a&gt; for their backend sounds like the"/>
						<outline text="attribute system in Frontier. We could use a great new sample site for Frontier 5. Hmmm."/>
						<outline text="&lt;/ol&gt;"/>
						</outline>
					</outline>
				<outline text="Send mail to dave@scripting.com."/>
				<outline text="This week's &lt;a href=&quot;http://www.zdnet.com/pcweek/spencer/spencer.html&quot;&gt;Spencer F. Katt&lt;/a&gt; has a couple of ">
					<outline text="juicy tidbits. Microsoft is doing a bundling deal for NT 5.0 with"/>
					<outline text="Marimba, and Apple is getting ready to acquire Silicon Graphics."/>
					</outline>
				</outline>
			<outline text="November 14" created="Fri, 14 Nov 1997 05:00:01 GMT">
